comments.body:
@jgillich I tried it first on my test/build vm which is a bit wonky at times, but it usually has the latest from upstream GitHub on it.  It worked there.

I tried on a fresh Fedora VM with Podman v1.0 on it and I ran into the same error running as root, so I think the issue isn't related to root/non-root user.  I installed Podman from upstream GitHub on that fresh VM and now the error isn't happeing.  I can't conclusively say so, but it looks like the issue has been fixed recently.

Any chance you can try cloning from GitHub and doing a make/make install and see if the problem is cured for you?
